                <head>No. 270<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>A report by the Secretary of the Interior and Petroleum Administrator for
                    Defense, entitled “National Security Problems Concerning Free World Petroleum
                    Demands and Potential Supplies,” dated December 2, was transmitted to the
                    Executive Secretary of the National Security Council. The report was submitted
                    to the National Security Council on December 8 for consideration at an early
                    Council meeting, and designated <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 138 on the
                    same day. (<gloss target="#t_SP1">S/P</gloss>–<gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                        >NSC</gloss> files, lot 61 D 167, “Free World Petroleum Demands and
                    Potential Supplies, National Security Problems Re <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                        >NSC</gloss> 138, 138/1”) For a summary, see <ref
                        target="frus1952-54v01p2#pg_1291">volume I, Part 2, page 1291</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
